#Text=Pocatello
#Text=Pocatello is a college town in Southeastern Idaho .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Named after a noted 19th-century Shoshoni chief , Pocatello is a working-class town with a strong railroad and trade union heritage .
#Text=As such it has more of a blue-collar feel to it than the other major Idaho cities .
#Text=At one time the city boasted the largest rail yard west of the Mississippi River .
#Text=The city has a reputation for being a ( slightly ) more progressive enclave in otherwise conservative , Mormon-dominated Eastern Idaho .

#Text=Although the presence of Idaho State University in Pocatello unquestionably makes it a college town as well , student life is somewhat more sedate than in other college towns in the region such as Moscow , Idaho , or Missoula , Montana .
#Text=The bar scene can be lively on the weekends , but do n't expect to find too many raging frat house keggers here .
#Text=Get in
#Text=Pocatello Regional Airport ( PIH ) , 1950 Airport Way .
#Text=Is served by regular flights from Salt Lake City on SkyWest Airlines .
#Text=There are no scheduled commercial flights to or from other locations in Idaho .
#Text=The airport in Idaho Falls , 45 minutes away , offers a more robust schedule .
#Text=Pocatello can be accessed by car via Interstate 15 from Idaho Falls in the north and Salt Lake City in the south .
#Text=Pocatello is the eastern terminus of Interstate 86 , which connects the city to the Twin Falls area in the west .
#Text=Despite its railroad heritage , Pocatello now has no passenger rail service .
#Text=For decades the railroad tracks have been used only for freight trains .
#Text=See
#Text=Idaho Museum of Natural History , ☏ +1208 282-3168 .
#Text=Do
#Text=Deleta - A rollerskating rink open at nights and during the day on non school days .
#Text=Also has laser tag , a play area , video games , and a food court .
#Text=Outer Limits - Video games , small indoor roller coaster , laser tag , food and a play area .
#Text=McKee 's - A pet store that also has an outdoor petting zoo .
#Text=One can pet goats , sheep , pigs , llamas , donkeys , turtles , see ostriches , emus , miniature horses , and even a deer along with lots of chickens .

#Text=Fort Hall Casino - Owned and operated by the Shoshone-Bannock Tribes , and located on the Fort Hall Indian Reservation north of Pocatello , Fort Hall Casino is the only legal gaming facility in southern Idaho .
#Text=Unlike in many Nevada casinos , where a minimum age of 21 is strictly enforced , 18-year-olds are allowed to gamble ( but not drink ) here .
#Text=Learn
#Text=Idaho State University is an important part of Pocatello .
#Text=Drink
#Text=First National Bar , ☏ +1208 233-1516 .
#Text=The in downtown Pocatello is a perennial favorite among ISU students and locals alike .
#Text=Known locally as simply the " First Nash , " the bar often features live blues music on the weekends .
#Text=Goody 's , 5th Avenue ( directly across from the ISU campus ) , ☏ +1208 233-9210 .
#Text=Doubles as a deli in the front and the bar in the back , both student favorites .
#Text=If someone says they 're going to the " Hindenburg , " ( the bar 's former name ) , they certainly mean here .
#Text=Camping
#Text=KOA-Pocatello , 9815 W Pocatello Creek Rd , ☏ +1 208-233-6851 .
#Text=Easy access to interstate .
#Text=Only 30 amp service available ; otherwise full hookups .
#Text=Cook-to-order breakfast for purchase by the park staff , very good food .
#Text=Stay safe
#Text=Pocatello tends to have more snow and more severe snowstorms than the other major cities in Idaho ( although not as severe as places like Stanley ) .
#Text=Given that and the city 's hilly landscape , driving can be a challenge in the winter .
#Text=The Pocatello area is also subject to inversions in the winter months .
#Text=This , combined with the output of nearby fertilizer plants , can make air quality an issue .
